STEP 3: CATALOG REQUEST FOR ADDING YOUR ID
TO GITHUB ENTERPRISE ACTIVE DIRECTORY GROUP
1. Digital Concierge Ticket
Click here to get to Digital Concierge and submit a catalog request to be added to the GitHub Active
Directory Group.
The Path is Order Things →Access to Systems →Other Systems →IT Systems
| 7
Now that you have a GitHub account
and your Kellogg email has been added
and verified, the next critical step is
getting added to the GitHub Enterprise
Active Directory Group. The
members of this Active Directory
group will be provided access to Kellogg
GitHub Enterprise Organization
STEP 01 STEP 02 STEP 03 STEP 04 STEP 05
STEP 3: CATALOG REQUEST
2. Filling in Catalog Request
a. Once within the Form, from the drop-
down for application, select “GitHub
Enterprise”.
b. Please view the image to the right for
the appropriate wording to use for
additional information as well as the
business justification needed to get
access to the directory.
c. Click on “Order Now”.
| 8
STEP 01 STEP 02 STEP 03 STEP 04 STEP 05
STEP 3: JOIN KELLOGG GITHUB
3. Accept the Invitation
Once the Active Directory group catalog request
is approved by your manager, you will get an
invitation from GitHub Kellogg Company
organization.
Click on the “Join @KelloggCompany” button.
| 9
STEP 01 STEP 02 STEP 03 STEP 04 STEP 05
STEP 4: TWO FACTOR AUTHENTICATION
1. Two factor authentication request
Click on the button to “Enable two factor authentication”. This
provides for enhanced security to your account.
| 10
2. Authentication Type
Select “Setup using App” or “Setup using SMS” button based on your
preference for Two factor Authentication. You need to install the required
App on your phone, if you pick the first choice. Typically, selecting “SMS” is
easier as long as you have your phone with you when authenticating.
2
STEP 01 STEP 02 STEP 03 STEP 04 STEP 05
STEP 4: RECOVERY CODES
1. Recovery Codes
2. SMS 2 Factor
Authentication
A list of recovery codes will
appear on the screen. Save
them somewhere on your
computer. These will come
in handy when you don’t
have your phone while
logging in.
a. If you selected
SMS option as your
two-factor
authentication
type, provide your
phone number in
the required space
and hit “Send
Authentication
Code”.
b. Once the text with
the code arrives on
your phone, enter
it here and then
hit “ Enable”.
